Hello,

Say you want to use Termius but are not allowed to store keys in the cloud vault. No problem. You can use hardware-based passkeys.

Passkeys are unextractable device-bound SSH keys. You can store them on a hardware security key or your device's secure subsystem.

🔑 *FIDO2.* Yubikeys and similar devices are often used for OTP. But they can also hold passkeys requiring your physical presence to connect. Generate a new FIDO2 key in Termius and use your hardware key to connect from mobile and desktop.

🫵 *Biometric keys.* Your phone and laptop can also store passkeys in their dedicated secure subsystem. Generate such keys in Termius and connect with your TouchID or FaceID.

⚠︎ Always have at least one *backup key* if the main one is lost.

